    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-25T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-25T22:00:00-05:00" n="692"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d692">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.116 Standard Vacuum Oil Co./63:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-26T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 26, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 27—4 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Standard Vacuum reports its vessel <hi rend="italic">Mei Heng</hi> machine
                    gunned October 19 in river at Changsha by Japanese airplane which dived over
                    ship. Vessel hit by fire but no injuries or deaths. Planes later <pb facs="0518"
                        n="514" xml:id="pg_514"/> machine gunned immediate vicinity Socony pontoons.
                    Vessels plainly identified as American. In Shanghai’s [1344] October 17, 6
                        p.m.,<note n="26a" xml:id="d692fn26a">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_185">p. 185</ref>.</note>
                    Japanese naval memorandum, paragraph 4, compliments Standard Oil Company on
                    steps taken to render its ships bearing on the question recognizable.</p>
                <p>Shanghai repeat to Tokyo. Repeated to Peiping, Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
